===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|trillion|lang=fr}}. From the prefix ''[[tri-]]'' (''three'') + ''[[-illion]]'' (from [[million]]); [[ie]] a [[million]] [[million]] [[million]].

Coined by [[w:Jehan Adam|Jehan Adam]] in 1475 as '''trimillion'''.<ref name="genevieve">Bibliothèque St Geneviève, Paris, MS Français 3143 - original French manuscript by Jehan Adam</ref> <ref name="parchemin">[http://www-bsg.univ-paris1.fr/la_reserve/expos/sciences/savants2.htm Jehan Adam, Traicté en arismetique pour la practique par gectouers… Parchemin. XVe siècle (1475).]</ref> <ref name="thorndike">Lynn Thorndike, “The Arithmetic of Jehan Adam, A.D. 1475,” Science and Thought in the Fifteenth Century</ref>
Rendered as '''tryllion''' by [[w:Nicolas Chuquet|Nicolas Chuquet]] in 1484, in his article “Triparty en la science des nombres”.<ref name="Chuquet1">
